My rapist helped me find another rental which was actually worse. I regret allowing him to help me out. All of this happened in the summer of 2016. The summer was the worse. I was just about to go back to school and I struggled with my addictions through school.

I want to add that before going forward with the second report, I had the courage and I was so stupid to even sit in his car for a second time but I was also desperate to find housing and I didn't want to be on the streets again.

The detective that took my case was super supportive and nice. He was patient and that's what I needed as I have trouble explaining myself. Also the social anxiety of just being in public and being "put on the spot" does not help.

When the city shut down the place, I eagerly went to get my stuff and I immediately looked for other rentals. I also made the report with the police again. the second time when I made the report, I felt a little bit better and more confident.

The place was shut down by the city about a month after the rape had happened. I was still at my friends house as I refused to even get my belongings. When I first made the report with the police when my manager helped me out, I had told the police to forget about the report.

I guess so that his wife didn't see but I'm sure maybe she suspected something? I'm not too sure. Out of all my room mates, I was the only one close to my landlords and in constant communication. I even attached myself to the land lady.

He bought me breakfast, made me coffee, and also brought lunch for me. Sometimes he would take me out to eat. Whenever we approached the house from the work site, he would take his hand off my leg - this was every time we got back home.

sweaters, and jewellery. He told me that he loved me and that I am like a daughter to him. Keep in mind, I never grew up with a fatherly figure and I've always dreamt of having a dad in my life. I think I attached myself to him and looked up to him as a parent which is fcuked up.

On top of work & the cleaning at my place, I felt like a maid - But on top of doing that, I would work in the mornings for about 8-12 hours at his construction company. He drove me from the house to the work site and then back home. He would buy me gifts such as sandals,
In my early 20s, I literally thought just a part time job was do-able to live on my own. It really isn't. You need a full time job. I'm not all there. I think you can tell.

On top of the cleaning, I was also balancing my work in retail and I barely got hours. I maybe got about 8 hours a week if I was lucky? During the busy season, they gave me 20 hours but that's still nothing.

Keep in mind - My mindset at the time was geared towards getting a rent discount. I was financially struggling. I did not have money. Social assistance, they don't give you anything because on top of rent, there's still other expenses to attend too and it just doesn't cut it.

because I guess they saw the sketchiness of the landlords but I didn't. I didn't clue in until I was raped. They made me sweep and mop the house and cut the lawn like every day. During the coldest winters and when it was snowing a lot, I had to go outside and shovel the driveway.

The relationship started off as just a landlord and a tenant relationship. And then I started working for the land lady as a maid in the house and my room mates told me not to do that and that they are only using me. Many room mates had moved out as a result of this and

One of my room mates I remember called me "stupid" for continuing to work with him. Am I really stupid? I didn't understand how things could have escalated to the way they did. I think I was trauma bonded to him and I think I still am. I'm still trying to wrap my mind around this

I thought this was a fair deal. I was also struggling financially on social assistance and I barely had the money to eat. So working for my rapist, I thought it ideal because the rent money I didn't have to pay would go towards food at least.

I guess I do blame myself for what happened to me. My room mates kept telling me to stop working for him and that he's only my landlord. I told my room mates that he's a good person and that I needed a rent discount. I did get my rent discount and on some months I didn't pay rent

The officer that took my report, I felt that she was judging me and I still remember her to this day. I was at that station for hours and they had me in one of those empty interrogation rooms and they were videoing me too.

That was step #1 and step #2 was to actually make the report and I wanted my manager to sit with me inside the room to make the report but I lied and told him that I was going to be okay. I was literally so emotional that day.
I was scared to even go back to my place to get my belongings. My manager from my retail job actually forced me to make a report and he drove me to the police station.

I didn't even want to make the report! When he raped me, I was about to start school and also find a new place to live. I stayed at an old friends house and he was all over me about reporting my landlord. I refused too and I was scared.

and that I didn't have my family. He knew exactly what he was doing and he set me up and I walked right into his trap. All I had was some pathetic video of him touching my leg and being all flirty while we were driving to one of the work sites.
